    &gt; to the test 
    &gt; class, it behaves as expected, printing the expected name 
    &gt; of the class and 
    &gt; exiting normally.
    &gt; 
    &gt;    public void testBadWrite() {
    &gt; 	try {
    &gt;        		
    &gt; PersistenceManager.singleton().write(&quot;insert into noSuchTable 
    &gt; values(&#39;hey&#39;)&quot;);
